    <abstract>
      <t>The Extension Mechanisms for DNS (EDNS(0)) [RFC6891] is explicitly defined to only have "per-message" semantics. This document defines a new Session Signaling OpCode used to carry persistent "per-session" type-length-values (TLVs), and defines an initial set of TLVs used to handle feature negotiation and to manage session timeouts and termination.</t>
